<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-12-04T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-12-04T00:00:00-05:00" n="718" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d718">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890.1115/6027: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Harrison</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Bern</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-12-04">December 4, 1942</date>.<lb/>[Received
                                    December 4—2:08 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5635. American interests—Far East, POW. Department’s 2048, August 27.
                                Swiss Minister Tokyo telegraphs December 1 following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                    <p>“My numerous endeavors obtain authorization visit prisoners
                                        of war camps [in] Japan, China [and] other territories
                                        occupied Japanese forces have prospects success. Japanese
                                        Foreign Office telephone[d] me today I would be authorized
                                        send delegates between December 3 and 10 to camps at Tokyo,
                                        Yokohama, Zentsuji, Keijo, Ginzen, Shanghai, Hong Kong and
                                        requested names these delegates. Hope later receive same
                                        authorization other camps.”</p></quote></p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Harrison</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>